The paper discusses a game theoretical approach to predicting outcomes of cyber-physical systems with multiple human interactions, which involves reinforcement learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.GT (Game Theory), cs.SY (Systems and Control), cs.LG (Machine Learning), and cs.MA (Multi-Agent Systems). However, since the paper focuses on the interplay between reinforcement learning and game theory, cs.AI and cs.GT are the most likely sub-categories. The other sub-categories are also relevant since the paper deals with systems and control, machine learning, and multi-agent systems.
